Note:
PATTERN LOWERING - HIR Patterns to MIR Comparison Values (P2-E Group B)

Pattern nodes (14000-14011) appear inside HIR_WHEN_CLAUSE bodies.
The enclosing HIR_MATCH_STATEMENT holds the scrutinee MIR value
in its frame; the WHEN_CLAUSE child_exit consumes the pattern's
emitted MIR value (a Boolean) and emits the compare-eq + branch
to the case_label or next_label.

The pattern handlers here emit the comparison value that the
WHEN_CLAUSE consumes. Each pattern type produces a different
comparison shape:

  HIR_IDENTIFIER_PATTERN (14000): always-true (binding pattern);
    binds the matched value to the variable id and pushes a
    constant 1 onto the result stack.
  HIR_LITERAL_PATTERN (14001): pushes a constant equal to the
    literal value; WHEN_CLAUSE then emits compare-eq vs scrutinee.
  HIR_TUPLE_PATTERN (14002): emits per-element compare-eq, ANDs
    them, pushes the AND result.
  HIR_RECORD_PATTERN (14003): per-field compare-eq + AND.
  HIR_WILDCARD_PATTERN (14004): always-true; pushes constant 1.
  HIR_TYPE_PATTERN (14005): type-check via runtime type-id
    compare.
  HIR_GUARD_PATTERN (14006): the guard expression's MIR value is
    AND-ed with the underlying pattern's result.
  HIR_RANGE_PATTERN (14007): emits start-le and le-end, ANDs them.
  HIR_VARIANT_PATTERN (14008): tag-compare against the variant
    discriminator.
  HIR_ARRAY_PATTERN (14009): per-element compare + length compare.
  HIR_OR_PATTERN (14010): per-alternative pattern OR'd together.
  HIR_REST_PATTERN (14011): always-true rest binding; pushes
    constant 1.

The current visit_pattern_children proc is being added by Wave H1
in parallel. Until it lands, these handlers are registered in
the dispatch table but will not be invoked (the visitor's
dispatcher routes through visit_node_children which calls
visit_pattern_children for pattern node types). Handlers must
work correctly the moment the visitor proc is added.
:End Note

Note: ============================================================
Note: IMPORTS
Note: ============================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir_nodes.runa" as MIRNodes
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/lowering/lowering_context.runa" as LCtx
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/mir/mir_builder.runa" as MIRBuilder
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_IDENTIFIER_PATTERN post handler (14000)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_IDENTIFIER_PATTERN post: binds the scrutinee value to the
variable id referenced by the pattern and emits an always-true
comparison value (constant 1) for the WHEN_CLAUSE to consume.
The actual binding happens via map_hir_to_mir_value so subsequent
body statements see the binding.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read variable_id at HIR_IDENTIFIER_PATTERN offset 16 (the
   symbol id of the binding).
2. Peek the enclosing MATCH frame to find the scrutinee MIR value
   at frame offset 16.
3. Map variable_id to the scrutinee value via map_hir_to_mir_value.
4. Allocate a true-constant value and push it as the comparison
   result.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Two emissions per identifier pattern (const + push).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Frame must be a MATCH frame; missing frame causes the binding to
be skipped (the body will reference an unmapped variable —
caught by validate_hir_tree).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_identifier_pattern_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If hir_node_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let builder_ctx be proc lowering_get_builder_ctx from LCtx with ctx
    If builder_ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let variable_id be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 16

    Let frame be proc cf_frame_peek from LCtx with ctx
    If frame is not equal to 0:
        Let match_value be proc cf_frame_get_field from LCtx with frame, 16
        If match_value is not equal to 0:
            If variable_id is not equal to 0:
                proc map_hir_to_mir_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, variable_id, match_value
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let true_value be proc allocate_temp_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx
    Let true_const be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with true_value, 1, 0, 0, 0
    If true_const is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_instruction from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, true_const
    End If
    proc lowering_push_result from LCtx with ctx, true_value

    Note: An identifier (variable-binding) pattern is irrefutable: it binds the
    Note: scrutinee and matches every value. Flag the MATCH frame (offset 48) so the
    Note: WHEN child_exit enters this arm unconditionally instead of comparing the
    Note: pushed constant against the scrutinee. The binding was already mapped above.
    If frame is not equal to 0:
        proc cf_frame_set_field from LCtx with frame, 48, 1
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_LITERAL_PATTERN post handler (14001)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_LITERAL_PATTERN post: emits the pattern's literal as a MIR
const. The WHEN_CLAUSE then compares it against the scrutinee.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read literal_value at HIR_LITERAL_PATTERN offset 8 and
   literal_type at the dedicated offset 48 (offset 16 is the
   HIRPattern bindings slot and must not be repurposed).
2. Emit MIR_CONST.
3. Push the value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Single emit per literal pattern.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Defensive null checks.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_literal_pattern_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If hir_node_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let builder_ctx be proc lowering_get_builder_ctx from LCtx with ctx
    If builder_ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let literal_value be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 8
    Let literal_type be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 48

    Let result_value be proc allocate_temp_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx
    Let const_inst be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with result_value, literal_value, literal_type, 0, 0
    If const_inst is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_instruction from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, const_inst
    End If

    proc lowering_push_result from LCtx with ctx, result_value
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_TUPLE_PATTERN post handler (14002)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_TUPLE_PATTERN post: emits per-element equality checks AND-ed
together. Each element pattern has already been visited and
pushed its comparison value onto the stack. We pop subpattern_count
values, AND them all, and push the result.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1. Read subpattern_count at HIR_TUPLE_PATTERN offset 24.
2. Pop subpattern_count values from the stack.
3. AND them sequentially (first AND second, then AND with third,
   etc.).
4. Push the final AND value.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
N-1 AND emissions per tuple pattern.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Zero-element tuple pattern produces a constant 1.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "lower_hir_tuple_pattern_post" that takes ctx as Integer, hir_node_ptr as Integer, node_type as Integer returns Integer:
    If ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If hir_node_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let builder_ctx be proc lowering_get_builder_ctx from LCtx with ctx
    If builder_ctx is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let subpattern_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with hir_node_ptr, 24

    If subpattern_count is equal to 0:
        Let true_value be proc allocate_temp_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx
        Let true_const be proc create_mir_const from MIRNodes with true_value, 1, 0, 0, 0
        If true_const is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_instruction from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, true_const
        End If
        proc lowering_push_result from LCtx with ctx, true_value
        Return 1
    End If

    Let depth be proc lowering_result_depth from LCtx with ctx
    Let to_pop be subpattern_count
    If to_pop is greater than depth:
        Set to_pop to depth
    End If

    Let accumulator be proc lowering_pop_result from LCtx with ctx
    Let popped be 1
    While popped is less than to_pop:
        Let next_value be proc lowering_pop_result from LCtx with ctx
        Let combined be proc allocate_temp_value from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx
        Let and_inst be proc create_mir_binary_op from MIRNodes with 20010, combined, accumulator, next_value, 0
        If and_inst is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_instruction from MIRBuilder with builder_ctx, and_inst
        End If
        Set accumulator to combined
        Set popped to popped plus 1
    End While

    proc lowering_push_result from LCtx with ctx, accumulator
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================
Note: HIR_RECORD_PATTERN post handler (14003)
Note: ============================================================

@Reasoning
HIR_RECORD_PATTERN post: per-field equality checks AND-ed
together. Same structural pattern as tuple-pattern.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Identical to tuple-pattern (count + AND chain).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
N-1 AND emissions per record pattern.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Zero-field record pattern produces a constant 1.
@End Security_Scope

